    "For the second Precondition slot filler, both approaches get a part of it but not the full slot filler, with the generative approach recognizing a slightly larger part of the actual slot filler.",
    "This is to some degree unexpected, as the mean performance of the extractive approach on the Population templates of the type 2 diabetes dataset is more than twice as high as the score of the generative approach.For the DiffBetweenGroups template, the extractive approach returns a perfect result in this case, whereas the generative approach misses the P < 0.001 slot filler but delivers a duplicate of the P = 0.013 slot filler.",
    "The mean results of Table 5 suggest similar performance, which is not the case here.For the Endpoint template instances, both approaches manage to extract most slot fillers at least partially but show issues grouping them together correctly.",
    "The extractive approach puts all of the extracted slot fillers in just two instances, missing most instances of the gold standard.",
    "For the generative approach, however, it is the other way around and too many instances (containing some duplicates) are generated."
